Course Introduction > About the course

Introduction

Hi there! Congratulations, you made it. You made a massive step in the learning process: "preparation," or what learning experts call "Arousing Interest." You are looking for resources and knowledge online, making you closer and more prepared to acquire the right skills and expertise to master a specific field. 

Attackers are not showing any indicators of slowing down. No matter the industry, there's no organization immune to attacks. The following stats from 'Cost of a Data Breach Report 2022, by IBM Security,' should give you an indication of how serious the situation is from a cyber defense perspective:

  • The average total cost of a data breach is USD 4.35 million.
  • 83% Percentage of organizations have had more than one breach.
  • 45% percent of breaches in the study occurred in the cloud.


CyberDefense has gone far beyond being an IT thing. Governments perceive it as a matter of national security and spend vast amounts of money and resources on improving their CyberDefense readiness. 

Cyber attackers are not attacking big and large size companies only. They target small businesses too. Do you know that according to 'Accenture's Cost of Cybercrime Study,' 43% of cyberattacks will aim at small business enterprises? Cybercriminals are attacking companies of all sizes, and your organization is a possible target regardless of size. 


This hands-on course is designed to take you through real-world techniques and tools. It will help you acquire the highly demanded cyber defense skills, preparing you for the professional market. The course will discuss theoretical concepts to help you understand the foundational basis of cyber defense and guide you through many hands-on labs to get a glimpse of cyber defenders' day-to-day job duties.

IBM, Cost of Data Breach report 2022


According to the 'IBM Cost of data Breach' report, the average time to detect a #breach is 207 days, plus 70 days to contain it, resulting in 277 days overall. For example, if a breach occurred on January 1st, it would take until July 27th to detect it and October 4th to contain it. The same report also highlights a widespread security skills shortage among organizations, and organizations that said their security teams had a skills shortage had a higher-than-average data breach cost as per the following graph:

IBM, Cost of Data Breach report 2022


Do you feel now how difficult it is to detect attacks and how severe is the lack of skilled defenders?

When developing course content, a great deal of attention has been given to efficiency (doing the right thing) and effectiveness (doing it right). Throughout the course, we will focus on technical domains that most defenders can utilize to get their cyber defense skills off the ground and maintain a reasonable level of cyber hygiene.

Please remember that this course, including the written content and videos, is being actively updated with new content, enhancements, or modifications. Therefore, the CyberDefenders team is open to any comments and suggestions, both technical and non-technical. Your feedback is priceless and will help other learners get the most out of this course.

Prerequisites

  • Solid understanding of Windows and Linux operating systems.
  • Reasonable research and problem-solving skills.
  • Familiarity with basic entry-level technology, networks, and security concepts.
  • Access to an enterprise environment is a plus.
